PART 7 — SECURITY RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
The following tables are NEVER referenced in any LLM prompt, ever: dpah_roles, dpah_user_roles, dpah_role_agent_access, dpah_collections, dpah_agents, dpah_modules, dpah_module_usergroups
Every LLM-generated SQL string must pass through sql_validator.py before db.execute() is called. No exceptions.
The database user executing analytics queries must have SELECT-only permissions. If a read-only DB user does not exist, create one before Week 1 Day 1: GRANT SELECT ON dpintranet.* TO 'analytics_reader'@'%' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';
Never return raw database error messages to the user. Catch all exceptions, log the full error server-side, return a safe generic message.
Row cap: never return more than 10,000 rows. result.fetchmany(10000).
Query timeout: configure at the MariaDB session level or use a 30-second application-level timeout.
